- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses reasoning steps to unpack the reduction relation of the calculus, which involves logical reasoning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the operational characteristics of the calculus and presents a novel abstract machine definition, which are relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the manipulation of a heap and the disciplined management of the evaluation stack, which are related to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper presents a simulation of call-by-need in a call-by-value language, which involves formal language concepts.
